snippet: There were 3,066 new contracts signed in the first quarter of the year, up 15 percent compared with 2012, according to StreetEasy.com, which also showed prices going up 26.8 percent.
abstract: All signs are pointing toward a seller's market in Manhattan real estate for the spring season, with inventory at near-record lows and prices inching up.
lead_paragraph: There were 3,066 new contracts signed in the first quarter of the year, up 15 percent compared with 2012, according to StreetEasy.com, which also showed prices going up 26.8 percent.

headline.seo: Prices and Sales Are Going Up in New York Real Estate, Brokers Say
headline.main: Real Estate Brokers Predict a Tough Time for Buyers
headline.print_headline: Real Estate Brokers Predict A Tough Time for Buyers
